<h1>Our Snake Game</h1>
<strong>Maximillion Jon Chua, Jesse Pan</strong>

<br>

<p>
    In our project, We were tasked with creating the client side for a multiplayer snake game. Functionally, Our snake game is the same as everybodys elses.
    Our game cycle is basically like, You spawn in and can eat and die. However, We added some comsmetic features that are different when compared to the provided
    example given. Our additional cosmetic features are that of a death image that triggers upon death. seperate snake skins that have custom drawn heads and tails.
    In addition to the ability of having seperate heads and tails for each snake skin. We also take in account of our snakes velicity and the correct orientation of each
    of the snakes head and tail. Which means if we go down then our head and tail faces down. 
    All of our assets that we use for the game is either hand drawn or pulled from the internet. 
</p>

<h4>Addition Functionality</h4>
<p>
    Custom Cosmetics
</p>
<p>
    The majority of our cosmetics that are like the backgrounds, walls and powerups have no specific programming implementations. They are generally just swap ins for 
    the provided snake assets. However, our snake cosmetics and our death animation have implementation that was specifically created for those features.
</p>

<p>
    <strong>Different Snakes</strong> Essentially, Our intention for this cosmetic feature is to have different snakes that are assigned to  the different IDs of each 
    indvidually added snakes. Since there is no limit on the ammount of snakes that we are allowed to have. We assign snake skins with the provided snake IDs modded by 8. 
    Since we drew 8 unique snakes. Our calculated IDs will result from 0-8. However, Since we draw snake's bodies with lines we also created snake heads and tails that are 
    related to each color of snake. In order to achieve this we had to create a helper method for both the snake head and the snake tail. Essentially, Its just a switch
    statement that returns the correct snake asset depending on the snakes skin ID. However,because of he fact that we assign pngs as the head and tail. We alos have to keep
    in account of the orientation of the snake. In order to achieve this. We first needed a clean way on draw a  rotated image. We made a helper method that saves thes state of 
    the canvas, then translates and moves the origin to the location of the head.  We then rotate the canvas to the desired angle and then draw the image then we restore the 
    original state. After figuring out how to draw thing rotated. We use the "dir" field from our playor model and draw based on the velocites. So if its (0,-1) then we rotate
    is up. If its (0,1) then we rotate down etc. It should be noted that since we are using a canvas coordinate system it does not match with a proper graph
    
    
</p>
    <p>
        <strong> death image </strong> this is generally a more simplier feature to implement. Essentially each time we draw a snake or player we check if the snake is alive
        and in the cases that the snakes are dead. We draw where the snake's heads position a explosion. So basically when any snake dies it leaves an explosion that stays until the 
        snake respawns or disconnects. 
        
