<h4>Development Details </h4>
<p>
    Geneerally, Our Networking code basically functions in this order. Our controller connects to the server that is inputted into our server address and port. After it successfully
    connects out controller accepts the JSON messages that the server sends to the the controller. After the controller receives the messages. We deserialize the messages and 
    parse its information into our made models. We decided what exact model to deserialize to by using Regex and seeing if key words lke "snake" "wall" or "powerups" appear.
    Once it finds out what type of message it is. We then format that information into our model. Our model is the type of World and our World contains 3 distict dictionarys
    that contain each snake, wall or power up that is present in the server. Each snake, wall, and power up contains information about their positions in the form of a model called
    Point2D.  Essentially when we render this information, Our View grabs this information from a copy of the GameWorld. We grab from a copy of the world rather than a gameworld,
    because of the fact that our GameWorld's data is always being modified since we deserialize servers packets and format it into our models. This is to prevent race conditions
    and accessing information from our dictionarys whilst they are being updated. We also use a object thats intention is to lock regions of code that mutate out gameworlds dictionarys
    inorder to prevent any race conditions. Our View generally works by after running our first render that renders the canvas, We run an asyncronous method calle game loop 
    that runs another asyncronous method called Draw frame, which essentially goes into our copy of the world and loops through each dictionary and renders all of the objects. 
    For the sake of readibility, We split rendering each object to helpermethods. We have 3 methods called drawPlayers,drawPowerups and drawWalls. All of which handle rendering
    each object in the given world.
</p>